                            <comment id="12916209" author="stuhood" created="Wed, 29 Sep 2010 17:30:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Targetting to 0.7.0: CF creation can be dangerous, and RAX needs to be able to lock it down.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12917996" author="urandom" created="Tue, 5 Oct 2010 14:36:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;See attached.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12918426" author="stuhood" created="Wed, 6 Oct 2010 05:36:19 +0000"  >&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;I think we need to minimize object creation in ClientState.hasColumnFamilyAccess: this was the intention of the member ArrayList&amp;lt;Object&amp;gt; in ClientState before, but I think it&apos;s more important now that it&apos;s called for every CF touch. Attaching an 0004 which we can consider in a different issue if you want.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Thanks for working on this Eric... much appreciated.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
